# AWS Repo Well-Architected Advisor — Rule-Driven Skill Routing

- Classify repo first: application, infrastructure, platform, GitOps, or mixed
- Default to standard review unless infrastructure, platform, GitOps, or regulated signals require deeper review
- Run skills in this order:
  - architecture-decision-engine
  - cloud-architecture-ai-auditor
  - security-review
  - networking-review
  - finops-cost-optimizer
  - observability-grafana-advisor
  - devops-review
  - nist-compliance-evaluator
  - aws-federal-grade-checklist
- Merge duplicate findings
- Preserve highest severity
- Preserve strongest confidence
- Never mark missing evidence as compliant
- If federal-grade checklist has CRITICAL findings → NOT READY
- If federal-grade checklist has HIGH findings → CONDITIONAL
- Missing required tags is a governance failure
- Prefer simplest safe AWS architecture
- Avoid EKS unless clearly justified
- Scaffold: "scaffold from this design", "generate IaC from findings" → aws-repo-scaffolder
- Design-and-implement: "read this repo and recommend", "ask requirements then code" → /design-and-implement or /solution-discovery → /platform-design → /scaffold
